724951f-a.title: Queens: 1st Street - Astoria Boulevard
724951f-a.text:
1st Street, east side, south from near Astoria Boulevard,
showing old homes on the East River waterfront. First Street
wasformerly Mills Street.
P. L. Sperr  June 12, 1935

726064f-a.title: Queens: Astoria Boulevard - 1st Street
726064f-a.text:
Astoria Boulevard, north side, between 1st and 2nd Streets,
showing the home of Samuel Noel, a watchmaker.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

726062f-b.title: Queens: Astoria Boulevard - 1st Street
726062f-b.text:
Astoria Boulevard, at First Street, on the East River, showing
the ferry house of the municipal femry operating to 92nd Street,
Manhattan. View 2 shows the old slips, which were replaced by new
Ones a few years later. Sean through one of the slips is the old
Wilson Hotel.
P. L. Sperr  March 9, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2

724950f-c.title: Queens: 1st Street - Astoria Boulevard
724950f-c.text:
1st Street, at, and adjoining the S. E. corner of Astoria
Boulevard. The corner house, which is boarded up, is the
Village Regular Democratic Club, according to P. L. Sperm.
It is a frame house, and the one contiguous to it is made of
brick.
P. L. Sperr  Views 1, 2: March 13, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIOPS  View 3: June 12, 1935
